<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-25T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-25T14:00:00-05:00" n="861" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d861">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115A Pacific War/440:
                                Airgram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-25T15:00:00-04:00">May
                                        25, 1943—3 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>A–170. American interests—Far East. Legation’s 2808 and 2805 of May
                                7. Department notes that Japanese authorities are reported in your
                                2805 to be prepared to permit visits to camps near Shanghai, while
                                it is reported in your 2808 that Swiss are unable to visit new
                                camps. Swiss Consul Shanghai should be informed of report from Tokyo
                                and request Gorgé’s assistance if necessary.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>